About the session

Beep Beep. Your salary has been credited. How much happiness does this message give? Now imagine this message coupled with a cute dancing teddy. Nobody would have thought a teddy can make your salary message even more fulfilling.
Advancements in technology are happening at an exponential rate - for many people keeping up with current tech can be overwhelming, and as an increasing number of systems and processes transfer to the online world, the general public is urged to follow suit. However, people often do not trust what they do not understand. When things become too complicated or hard to understand some people will choose not to use it or daring not to touch it, alternatively they merely memorize one function and setting and try to ignore the rest.
Welcome to the world of micro-interactions. Micro-interactions is about the criticalities that make the difference between friendly experience and traumatic anxiety. The devil is in the details. Of course, the big picture is outstanding, but lack of attention to the details can lead to a frustrating and disappointing experience. Details can make engaging with the product more easier and user-friendly, for which micro interactions pave the way. Focusing on them is the way to create the future of user-focused design and experience!

Who should attend?

  • Full Stack Designers: 0 - 4 Years
  • Graphic Designers: 0 - 4 Years
  • Visual/Graphic Artists: 0 - 3 Years
  • Creative Artists: 0 - 3 Years
  • UI Designers: 0 - 4 Years

Session Level: Basic to intermediate.
Others: Non Designers or any Design enthusiasts and the believer in designs can attend this session.
